snippet.title: THIS IS KOTOR MONTENEGRO! Travel Vlog | Sophies Suitcase
snippet.description:
Welcome to KOTOR MONTENEGRO everybody! During my cruise on board the Sky Princess we visited Kotor, Montenegro and I have to say it’s one of the most underrated places I have ever visited. Before this cruise I had never thought of visiting Montenegro but when I did some research I realised how beautiful it was and a few friends recommended some places to visit. We decided to spend half the day hiking up to the fortress Castle of San Giovanni and then headed across to the most beautiful island of Our Lady of the Rocks in the afternoon. ADD THIS PLACE TO YOUR BUCKET LIST!

*press trip in association with Princess Cruises.

During the trip I headed to:
- Italy
- Montenegro
- Greece

Check out my guide to Kotor Montenegro: https://sophiessuitcase.com/2019/12/02/european-cruise-itinerary-sky-princess-inaugural-cruise-and-shore-excursions/

#skyprincess #princesscruises #kotormontenegro

snippet.title: HOW TO: Hong Kong Lion Rock Hike (2019 Travel Vlog)
snippet.description:
Today we show you step by step how to do the famous must-do Lion Rock Hike in Hong Kong!

The views from the top are absolutely amazing though the journey to get there isn't for the faint of heart. We got a good workout in making the trek up and want to give you a guide if you are planning a hike too! Plus we eat some delicious dim sum as a reward after the hike, also a must when in Hong Kong.

We tried our best to capture our experience but if you have questions feel free to comment below! :)

snippet.title: Exploring a working farm in COSTA RICA RAINFOREST | TRAVEL VLOG
snippet.description:
The sun has finally come out and we're just about settled in our new home in Costa Rica! Today we jump on our bikes and explore some botanical gardens in and around the lush Costa Rica rainforest surrounding us in Finca La Isla!

The nature here in Costa Rica is stunning, there is wildlife absolutely everywhere you look Today was extra special as we took our first steps into the dense Costa Rica rainforest. We saw a ton of tropical fruits growing, a walking palm and a red poison dart frog! Needless to say, it was a fantastic day.

Music:
The New Fools - We'll Do It All
Dye O - Bloom
Spring Gang - You Left Behind (Instrumental Version)

snippet.title: Wilsons Promontory National Park, Australia | Travel Vlog | Travel More
snippet.description:
Wilsons Promontory National Park is on a peninsula southeast of Melbourne, Australia. It’s known for its rugged granite mountains and abundant wildlife, including kangaroos and wombats. Trails from the Tidal River settlement lead to Squeaky Beach, with its white quartz sand. Nearby, Mount Oberon offers views of Bass Strait and offshore islands.

Video & Edit by Chathura Chinthaka Bandara
